This is actually a **new and very strong clue**.

Previously you had:

```text
NoSuchFieldError:
JsonFormat$Feature.READ_UNKNOWN_ENUM_VALUES_USING_DEFAULT_VALUE
```

Now you have:

```text
NoSuchMethodError:
com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty.namespace()
```

This proves one thing with almost 100% certainty:

> **Your `jackson-databind` and `jackson-annotations` versions are still mismatched at runtime.**

`JsonProperty.namespace()` was introduced in newer versions of `jackson-annotations`, but your application is loading an older `jackson-annotations.jar` while `jackson-databind` is expecting the newer method.

This is no longer a Gradle build issue.

This is a **runtime classpath issue**.

